problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in engineering would. In the five-sided star shown, the letters $A$, $B$, $C$, $D$, and $E$ are replaced by the numbers $3$, $5$, $6$, $7$, and $9$, although not necessarily in this order. The sums of the numbers at the ends of the line segments $AB$, $BC$, $CD$, $DE$, and $EA$ form an arithmetic sequence, although not necessarily in this order. What is the middle term of the sequence?

[asy]
unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E;

A = dir(90);
B = dir(90 + 3*360/5);
C = dir(90 + 6*360/5);
D = dir(90 + 9*360/5);
E = dir(90 + 12*360/5);

draw(A--B--C--D--E--cycle);
filldraw(Circle(A,0.15),white);
filldraw(Circle(B,0.15),white);
filldraw(Circle(C,0.15),white);
filldraw(Circle(D,0.15),white);
filldraw(Circle(E,0.15),white);

label("$A$", A);
label("$B$", B);
label("$C$", C);
label("$D$", D);
label("$E$", E);
[/asy]
